# Match arms that leave different types on the stack join into a single
# union value (`int | float`) that flows forward, rather than fanning out
# as alternative typings. A non-empty list takes the `_ :> sum` arm (int);
# an empty list takes the `[]` arm (float).
[1 2 3] match []: 0.0, _ :> sum end full!
[] match []: 0.0, _ :> sum end empty!

# Overload resolution distributes the `int | float` union across numeric
# builtins: it checks every member against the candidate overloads, so a
# generic consumer is not required. numFmt's (int dict) / (float dict)
# overloads both apply, and toFloat's (int -- float) / (float -- float)
# arms resolve the union to float for the division below.
@full { 'decimals': 0 } numFmt wl
@empty { 'decimals': 1 } numFmt wl
@full toFloat 2.0 / 1 toFixed wl
